sentences: Randy Parsons (born 1965) is an American luthier whose client list includes Jack White, Jimmy Page, Sammy Hagar, Death Cab for Cutie, Peter Frampton, Joe Perry, and Modest Mouse.
Until 2013 he worked out of his main shop in Seattle, which was run by five women, three of whom are luthiers.
In August 2013, Parsons moved with his main shop to Ventura, California.
A documentary short film about Parsons, Randy Parsons: American Luthier, premiered at the ITSA Film Festival at the Historic Sonoma Opera Hall on October 1, 2011.
It was nominated for an Emmy Award in April, 2015.
